title: MAFS' Dan Webb says Jessika Power will 'wreck' Love Island
text:
Dan Webb has taken a nasty swipe at his ex-girlfriend Jessika Power.

In an interview with Who magazine, the Married At First Sight cheater was less than kind when asked about rumours that Jess could join Love Island Australia as an intruder this season.

'I wonder if Jess will roll on in,' the 35-year-old said. 'It would probably wreck the show.'

'It would probably wreck the show': Dan Webb says that ex-girlfriend Jessika Power would ruin Love Island Australia if she joins the show as an intruder

Despite slamming Jessika's prospects on the show, Dan himself said that he'd love to appear on the reality TV dating series.

'Sign me up to Love Island!' he gushed, before admitting that he's probably 'too old' to get on the show now.

'Maybe I could change my passport details and get in there,' he mused.

'Sign me up to Love Island!' After slamming Jess, Dan kicked off his own campaign to get cast on the reality TV dating series - but admitted that he's probably 'too old' now to make the cut

Dan's best mate Adam Farrugia as well as his ex-girlfriend Vanessa Sierra, 24, are both starring on Love Island this year.

In an awkward turn of events, Vanessa's ex-boyfriend is Jessika Power's older brother Rhyce.

Rumours have swirled for months that Jessika could potentially join this season of Love Island as an intruder.

Bombshell: Rumours have swirled for months that Jessika could potentially join this season of Love Island as an intruder

In a recent interview with The Kyle and Jackie O Show, the outspoken blonde said that she's keen to gatecrash the series so she can confront rival Vanessa.

Referring to Vanessa, Jessika said: 'When the [Love Island] promo came out I was just like, "Oh, that's why the social climbing is happening".

She also revealed that Vanessa had been 'slagging' her on social media with disparaging comments.

Love Island Australia airs nightly on Channel Nine and is available to stream on 9Now.
description: Dan Webb has taken a nasty swipe at his ex-girlfriend Jessika Power.
